{#title .lead}
# Q2 Was a Good Quarter

{#byline}
Acme Research — June 25, 2026

{#rev-para}
Revenue grew 12% quarter over quarter, the fastest pace in two years. Cloud
carried the result while Devices softened, and operating margin expanded by
180 basis points as the cost program landed ahead of schedule.

{#fig-rev}
![Revenue by segment, Q1 vs Q2, in billions USD.](assets/chart-revenue.svg)

{#seg-head}
## Segment detail

{#seg-para}
Cloud reached $4.6B (up from $4.1B) on strong renewals and a full quarter of the
Northwind acquisition. Devices slipped to $1.9B as the channel worked down
inventory; we expect a return to growth in Q3 as the new line ships.

{#fin-table}
| Segment | Q1 ($B) | Q2 ($B) | QoQ   |
|---------|--------:|--------:|------:|
| Cloud   |     4.1 |     4.6 | +12%  |
| Devices |     2.0 |     1.9 |  −5%  |
| Total   |     6.1 |     6.5 |  +7%  |

:::warning
{#guidance-note}
Forward guidance assumes no change to current tariff schedules. A material
change would be disclosed in an 8-K.
:::

{#outlook-head}
## Outlook

{#outlook-para}
We are raising full-year revenue guidance to a range of $26.5B–$27.0B and
reiterating our margin target. The Q3 priorities are the Devices refresh and
continued Cloud gross-margin expansion.
